review_content:
Fresh Earthy-Green-Citrus w/ a hint of Spiciness & Aquaticness

doesn't stray far from the original Mr.Burberry EDT just more of an aquatic version.
opening smells exactly like chrome aqua same rindy citrus (lemon+bergamot+grapefruit) & sharp herbal-greenness (basil+mint, makes a clove like accord);
mid-dry resembles JV Artisan Blu, as tea & light violet (slightly powdery) comes out along with "water notes" to cut the green-herbal-spiciness some and bring a slight aquatic accord;
fully dry is slightly aquatic/watery with a hint of earthiness (like a lighter AdG Profumo) but almost undetectable;
versatile, can be worn year round, day or night, casual or office but not mass appealing imo due to its sharpness;

Projection/Sillage': MILD, arms length scent bubble for the 1st 1-2 hours, then mostly an close scent.

Performance/Longevity: GOOD, about 8-9 hours (on fabric).

@Rose du soir, beautifully written! However, peach stands out the most to me. Otherwise, I agree: it´s woody, earthy, and especially mossy...warm and sexy in a cheeky way.
I loved to use this one during cooler rainy, foggy days in spring and fall. I remember a particular afternoon in late autumn a few years back when I went with my friends for a cup of hot chocolate into a newly opened, very cozy, and stylish cafeteria. One gentleman came to me and said I smell nice 🍑
Again one of the great creations of the '90s.
